<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=shoop&Board=monk&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=Session&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View shoop (shoop) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Pros: You are all of like mind.....uhm....err...cant think of any others<p>

Cons: You are all the same class and all will need nearly the same gear.<br>
      There is no way that you will be able to form a strong group with<br>
          just guild members (assuming you stay true to all monks) and <br>
          will have to rely heavily on outside help.<br>
      Nobody in your guild will be able to teleport<br>
         or bind people<br>
         or sow people<br>
         or resurrect people<br>
         or any other number of things that are class limited<p>

<br>
 Sure you can have a sister guild that can complete what you are lacking...which is everything but the karate kicks(HIIIYAA!@!)...but why not just have a guild that is balanced?    I wouldnt take my monk down a dangerous doungoun with a full group of monks, it wouldnt take long before we all have to FD or die trying.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
